The paper deals with the generalization error of learned predictors, which is a central topic in machine learning. The use of surrogate predictors and derandomization techniques to control generalization error is a common approach in the field, which suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of conditioning and denoising techniques, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The examples studied in the paper involve interpolating predictors, which are often associated with computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS).
